<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-25T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-25T07:00:00-05:00" n="749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/1291: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-25T15:00:00+03:00">March 25,
                                1941—3 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received March 25—12:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>587. The Moscow press today publishes an official announcement stating that
                        yesterday Matsuoka accompanied by Tatekawa was received by Molotov and that
                        Stalin was present at the meeting which lasted more than an hour.</p>
                    <p>The press also reports the departure of Matsuoka for Berlin last evening.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>